data.title: State of Emergency declared in New York City over flash flooding
data.description: Parts of New York were under water on Friday as torrential rainfall caused severe flash flooding across the city and a state of emergency was declared. A large storm system settled over the city on Thursday night, leaving the five boroughs and parts of upstate New York, New Jersey and Connecticut under flood watches and warnings.

data.title: There's been friction with Canada since 1980s, discussed issue with US: Jaishankar
data.description: External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar said he expressed concerns over the ongoing diplomatic row with Canada to US NSA Jake Sullivan and Secretary of State Antony Blinken. I think hopefully we both came out better informed, he said. This has been an issue of great friction for many years with Canada, in fact going back to the 1980s, Jaishankar added.
